  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Fisher &amp; Paykel in LA — NZ engineering with Huntington Beach parts-chain</h2>
    <p>F&amp;P's LA service positioning differs from other luxury brands in one practical way: parts logistics actually work. Most luxury oven brands (Sub-Zero/Wolf Madison WI, Middleby Viking Greenwood MS, Miele Princeton NJ) ship parts from thousands of miles away, which means 3-7 day wait on common components + longer on specialty items. F&amp;P USA's Huntington Beach distribution center sits roughly 35-50 miles from most LA service addresses. Common F&amp;P oven parts — thermal sensors, bake elements, convection fan motors, door hinges, gaskets, pyrolytic door lock motors, CombiSteam descaling kits — often arrive next-day or same-day. Specialty items (Series 9 flush-mount color-matched panels, specific generation control boards) still route through NZ factory with 2-4 week lead, but the volume-80 parts base is LA-responsive.</p>
    <p>Our LA F&amp;P oven service geography concentrates in West LA design-forward custom kitchens — Pacific Palisades canyon + coastal, Brentwood established luxury, Mar Vista + Venice modernist remodels, Santa Monica coastal, Hancock Park historic-homes with updated kitchens, and Pasadena + San Marino mid-luxury. Series 9 flush-mount installations tend to concentrate in custom-built 2010+ kitchens where the F&amp;P matched-suite aesthetic was specified at design stage (refrigerator + cooktop + ventilation + oven all coordinated). Contemporary built-ins appear in developer-spec luxury-tier new construction and mid-luxury renovation across the broader LA basin.</p>
    <p>The brand's engineering heritage matters for service judgment. NZ engineering leans toward <b>serviceability</b> — F&amp;P designs historically favor component-level repair over full-assembly replacement (door hinge pairs are serviceable individually, control boards can be replaced without swapping the user interface, pyrolytic lock motors are discrete serviceable parts). This contrasts with some brands that push full-assembly replacement for relatively minor component failures. In practice, F&amp;P oven service economics tend to land lower than peer luxury brands on equivalent failures because the repair path is genuinely component-level rather than assembly-level.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Fisher &amp; Paykel oven failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Thermal sensor drift (Pyrolytic cycles accumulate wear)</h3><p>Most common F&amp;P oven call. Thermal sensor drifts after many pyrolytic cycles — sensor survives 900°F but accuracy degrades over 6-10 years of regular pyrolytic use. Swap $145-$215. Calibration verification at diagnostic using cavity thermocouple vs sensor reading.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Pyrolytic door lock motor failure</h3><p>F&amp;P-specific. Lock cycles under thermal stress every pyrolytic run (locks below 500°F, unlocks below 500°F). Motor fatigue appears at 7-12 years of regular pyrolytic use. Swap $225-$325.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Bake element or convection ring element</h3><p>Element failure pattern by mode. Bake-only fail → bake element $245-$345. Convection-only fail → convection fan motor $285-$425 OR ring element $285-$425, diagnostic differentiates.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>CombiSteam scale buildup (LA hard water)</h3><p>Annual descaling $185 flat. When scale has progressed past descaling threshold: steam generator element $345-$485 or water inlet valve $245-$345.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door hinge wear — Series 9 flush-mount tighter spec</h3><p>Contemporary hinges at 8-12 years, Series 9 at 10-15 years with flush-mount precision requirement. Pair replacement $320-$460 Contemporary, $425-$585 Series 9.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Control board failure at 10-14 years</h3><p>F&amp;P-generation-specific control boards, $385-$580. Huntington Beach parts-chain on common generations; specialty generations route through NZ factory at 2-4 week lead.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Fisher &amp; Paykel oven product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Series 9 Professional (flagship, flush-mount)</h3><p>OB30 / OB24 flush-mount built-in wall ovens with matched-suite integrated aesthetic. West LA custom-kitchen concentration. Color-matched panel + flush-mount hinge architecture differentiates service from Contemporary.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Contemporary built-in</h3><p>OB30 / OB24 Contemporary tier mainstream built-in. Standard cabinet opening, visible stainless or black. Mid-luxury renovation + developer-spec new construction concentration across LA basin.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pyrolytic self-clean signature</h3><p>F&amp;P's defining tech — 900°F cavity self-clean, 1.5-3 hour cycle. Distinct from steam-clean systems. Door lock + thermal sensor wear patterns differ from non-pyrolytic ovens.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>CombiSteam (steam + convection hybrid)</h3><p>OS30 / OS24 CombiSteam series — steam generator + convection fan + bake element in one cavity. Water reservoir fill. LA hard-water descaling 6-12 month intervals.</p></div>
