  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>F&amp;P oven vs Miele vs Sub-Zero Wolf — LA luxury built-in comparison</h2>
    <p><b>Fisher &amp; Paykel (this page)</b> — NZ-engineered, Haier-owned, Huntington Beach warehouse. Pyrolytic self-clean signature + CombiSteam hybrid. LA-local parts advantage vs peer luxury brands. Series 9 flush-mount + Contemporary tiers.</p>
    <p><b>Miele</b> — German family-owned since 1899, Princeton NJ distribution (2,800 miles from LA). MasterChef auto-programs signature + DG pure steam + DGC CombiSteam hybrid. Premium positioning above F&amp;P. See <a href="/brands/miele-oven-repair/">Miele oven repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Sub-Zero / Wolf</b> — Wisconsin family-owned, Madison WI distribution (2,000 miles). Wolf M Series + E Series wall ovens + CSO Convection Steam Oven. Suite positioning with Sub-Zero refrigeration. See <a href="/brands/wolf-oven-repair/">Wolf oven repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Bosch / Thermador / Gaggenau</b> — BSH German portfolio, Irvine CA warehouse (LA-local, comparable advantage to F&amp;P Huntington Beach). 300/500/800 Series + Benchmark + Masterpiece + 400 Series Gaggenau. See <a href="/brands/bosch-oven-repair/">Bosch</a> · <a href="/brands/thermador-oven-repair/">Thermador</a>.</p>
    <p>Parts networks exclusive — no cross-reference. Choice drivers for F&amp;P: households wanting premium NZ engineering + LA-local parts speed + pyrolytic self-clean without full Miele premium.</p>
  </div></section>

